rename used with the switch options
Example:
ls 
abc.txt  file33.txt  file42.txt
rename 's/\.txt/\.png/' *.txt
ls
abc.png  file33.png  file42.png

Example: 
rename 's/file/documnet/' *.png
ls
abc.png  document33.png document42.png


RHEL/Fedora Rename Example:
rename .conf .backup *.conf
(changes all files with .conf into .backup files)

Example: 
rename one THREE *
(changes any occurrence of one into THREE)


(using option -vn will not make any chnages but will display the 
changes made when the operation if performed without the options)
Example:
reanme -vn tail tails *
OUTPUT:
'tail' -> 'tails'
